The White House Press Secretary, Jay Carney, announced that President Obama will be giving a speech at Knox College about the economy and the need to expand the middle class. Carney stated that the President believes it is an appropriate time to address these issues and that Washington has been distracted from the concerns of the American people. The President hopes that his speech will refocus attention on the economy and the need to invest in the middle class. Carney also mentioned that the President is cautiously optimistic about the progress made in the Middle East peace process and believes that resolving the Israeli-Palestinian conflict would have positive effects beyond the conflict itself. In addition, Carney stated that the President is concerned about the situation in Egypt and believes that all politicized arrests and detentions should end.